0.2.3: Changed return codes to be bash compatible (normal exit returns 0, error returns 255).

       Changed printf to fprintf(stderr, ... (errors) and fprintf(stdout, ... (transformed text)
       to eliminate security problems from buffer overruns.

       Improved code legibility for debugging and maintenence.

       Changed int to int32_t to improve portability.

0.2.2: Implemented ESC [ # d and ESC [ # e vertical cursor positioning
       Corrected erase screen/line not clearing mode information correctly

0.2.1: First Release

